title: Iowa Cycling's 3rd Annual Hawkeye Horseshoe Hootenanny
Chris Lillig Memorial Cup/Old Capitol Criterium
Race Like a Girl
description: Race Like A Girl is a "laid back" circuit race on about a 1/2 mile loop in Union Park in Des Moines. The race is designed of offer opportunities for new racers as well as the more experienced racers. Race includes Women's B, Mens B and Women's A, Men's A, Juniors, and a kiddy race. Races are track-style formats, ie. 10 laps, points every other lap. The format will be explained before each race.
course: 1/2 mile paved loop, mostly flat. One small rise about 2/3 through the course. Shade and lawn to sit and watch the race. Very family friendly venue.
registration: Register day of race. USA Cycling annual license or 1-day license required. Kiddies need to also register. All USCF rules apply, helmets required, included for kids in the kiddy race. Big wheels, trikes, training wheels are fine for the kiddy race. Older kids may choose to race in the junior race.
notes: Registration opens at 4:30 p.m., Races start at 5:30 p.m., and generally will finish as darkness nears. Each racer will have a chance to race at least 3 times during the evening. No prize money, just schwag (prizes). Kiddies get cookies and medals.
directions: Union Park is located in Des Moines, just north of Lutheran Hospital and just south of Birldland Marina. We race on the south loop. The street is Saylor Road. Easiest to GoogleMap Union Park Des Moines https://www.google.com/search?q=union+park+des+moines&sourceid=ie7&rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&ie=&oe=&rlz=

title: Junction 21 Time Trial Race and Ride
Junction 21 Time Trial Race and Ride
Oktemberfest Criterion
course: We have a .85 mile course on city streets in a figure eight.  Enjoy the downtown area of Marshalltown.
registration: Register at www.usacycling.com or register day of event at least 20 minutes prior to race time.
notes: Race starts in front of county courthouse turning south on Center Street, west on Church Street, north on 1st Street, east on Main Street, north on Center Street, east on State Street, south on 2nd Avenue, and west on Main Street.
directions: Coming into Marshalltown fron Highway 14 - turn west on State Street for parking, registration is south 1 block on Main Street across from county courthouse.

title: Park Farm Gravel Grinder
description: Park Farm Gravel Grinder...Cycle Cross or Road Bicycle will be great for this course (as long as it doesn't rain too much), Mountain, Single Speed, Fat Tire all will be scored and placed! Juniors/Women/Masters top 3 fastest will receive a medal too!
course: 17 and 33 Mile Loops. Total Distance is 50 Miles. Paved and Unpaved Roads, Most Gravel is uphill, with a couple of exceptions.
notes: All Racers will roll out at 10:00 A.M. (Except Juniors, they will depart a few minutes later, they only race 17 miles versus the 50 for everyone else).
directions:
Park Farm Winery, 15159 Thielen Rd, Bankston, IA 52039
The winery is located in Dubuque County. The easiest reference point is the city of Dubuque, Take Hwy 20, exit at Peosta (Sundown Road), Right on Sundown,  Left on Old HWY 20 Proceed 1/2 mile, Right on Girl Scout Road, Right onto Graf Rd and continue straight onto Theilen Road (3  miles north to the Winery). Note: Winery is about 6 miles from Hwy 20.
